          <type>const std::vector&lt; std::string &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>commandArgs</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Pure parse: scans <computeroutput>commandArgs</computeroutput> for MCP-related flags and returns the resolved overrides. Last occurrence of each flag wins (matches shell convention). <computeroutput>-mcpPort N</computeroutput> forces the server port to N (overriding the config). <computeroutput>-mcpDumpFile &lt;path&gt;</computeroutput> requests writing the tool cache to that path; the caller (typically <computeroutput><ref refid="group__GeneralGroup_1gaf6506d80121763c6d296ced7af498180" kindref="member">ViewerSetup::setupMcp</ref></computeroutput>) is expected to skip starting the live server in that case so a prime spawn does not collide with a real backend on the port. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
